{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἄρκτος</b>, ἡ, <br /> <b>bear,</b> especially <b>Ursus arctos, brown bear,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 11.611, “hymnus ad Mercurium” 223, “hymnus ad Venerem” 159, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.191, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: the instances of the <i>masculine</i> are uncertain [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"(4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Coloribus” 798a26 is inconclusive)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>], the <i>feminine</i> being used even when both sexes are included, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “HA” 539b33. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> Ἄρκτος, ἡ, the constellation <b>Ursa Major,</b> Ἄρκτον θ᾽, ἣν καὶ Ἄμαξαν ἐπίκλησιν καλέουσιν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.487, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 5.273, compare 1st c.AD(?): Heraclitus 120, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 1154, etc.; τὰ ὑπὸ τὴν Ἄ. ἀοίκητα 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.10; Ἄρκτου στροφάδες κέλευθοι 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 131 (Lyric poetry); Ἄρκτου στροφάς τε καὶ Κυνὸς ψυχρὰν δύσιν [prev. author] “fragment” 432.11\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: in <i>plural</i>, <b>the Greater and Lesser Bears,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Aratus Epicus 27\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; Ἄ. μικρά, μεγάλη, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 2.5.35, 36, compare 1st c.BC: Cicero, M. Tullius Orator et Philosophus “de Natura Deorum” 2.41.105. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>the north,</b> πρὸς ἄρκτον τετραμμένος[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.148, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 733 (Lyric poetry), 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 3.165, etc.; ἀπὸ ἄ. “IG” 5(2).444.11 (from Megalopolis), +others: _plural_, 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Aër.” 5 and 19, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Critias” 118b, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__3.b</b></Level4> ἡ ἑτέρα ἄ. <b>the south pole,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 362a32. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> ἄρκτος, ἡ, at Athens <b>a girl appointed to the service of Artemis Brauronia</b> or Ἀρχηγέτις, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hyps.fragment” 57, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 645. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> a kind of <b>crab,</b> probably <b>Scyllarus arctus,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 549b23, compare 4th c.BC: Speusippus Philosophus cited in 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 3.105b, 4th c.BC: Mnesimachus Comicus 4.45, 4th c.BC: Archestratus Epicus “fragment” 56. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> ἄρκτου δένδρον, ={ἀκτῆ}, Ps.-[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 4.173\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]. (Cf. Sanskrit <i>ṛk[snull]as,</i> Latin <i>ursus,</i> etc.)","strongNumber":"G0715","accentedUnicode":"ἄρκτος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0714","matchingForm":"ἀρκέω","stepTransliteration":"arkeō","gloss":"be sufficient","_zh_tw_Gloss":"夠","_es_Gloss":"ser suficiente","_zh_Gloss":"够"}],"shortDef":"bear","mediumDef":"bear <br />bear, constellation of Ursa Major","stepGloss":"bear","stepTransliteration":"arktos","count":0,"_es_Definition":"oso ","_zh_tw_Definition":"熊 (啟 13:2)","_zh_Definition":"熊 (启 13:2)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"con gấu","_zh_tw_Gloss":"熊","_es_Gloss":"oso","_zh_Gloss":"熊"}]}